I tested the code in Rainier system.

The power supply device driver abstracts the 'pmbus LED' and represents it as a standard /sys/class/leds/ LED. From the user space code perspective, this power supply LED, which essentially receives i2c/pmbus commands to set its behavior, appears just like any other LED.

Power supply LEDs in Rainier:
root@p10bmc:/sys/class/leds# ls cffps*
cffps2-68:
cffps2-69:
cffps2-6a:
cffps2-6b:


Config files:
